{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02743/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02743"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:27:43"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman smells another woman."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02743","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02743"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1/d1003d06-0886-4914-966b-2f62a7225758","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:37:59.203Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As Cyril pulls in to smell Alma, the camera switches to a close-up, allowing viewers to experience the intrusion.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:828.9441829186281,436.05917955615337,450.62542030934776,445.4606590450571"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1/fefced36-f823-43e3-9e13-ffaa867bd741","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:38:15.652Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Cyril gets up onto the pedestal Alma stands on, placing the two of them on the same footing in a very literal sense. She asserts her dominance over Alma, showing her that she is not above Cyril.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:825.0706119704103,86.14660390047081,480.32279757901824,214.33759246805644"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1/2528e781-4aa1-4266-b50c-a467616d657a","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:38:55.170Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Cyril immediately smells Alma, attempting to identify the specific ingredients of her scent. This calls back to Reynolds’s <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW167121790 BCX4\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-01014.html\"><u>description of his dreams of his mother</u></a>, where he specifically emphasizes that he can smell her scent. In connecting the two women by their association with distinctive smell, the film foreshadows Alma’s maternal figure in Reynolds’s life.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02743/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1329.9260255548083,380.5379959650303,228.54068594485534,502.27303295225295"}}}]}]}]}